{"nbformat":4,"nbformat_minor":0,"metadata":{"colab":{"provenance":[{"file_id":"19zVZ5ae4cPvxDn0pY_uyFZ10BD2YRXkk","timestamp":1756918534658}]},"kernelspec":{"name":"python3","display_name":"Python 3"},"language_info":{"name":"python"}},"cells":[{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["Experiment 4\n","\n","Theory:\n","Overloading and Overriding in Python are the two main object-oriented concepts that allow\n","programmers to write methods that can process a variety of different types of functionalities with\n","the same name. This helps us to implement Polymorphism and achieve consistency in our code.\n","Let's look at an example to understand the concept of overloading and overriding:\n","Method Overloading in Python is a type of Compile-time Polymorphism using which we can\n","define two or more methods in the same class with the same name but with a different parameter\n","list.\n","We cannot perform method overloading in the Python programming language as everything is\n","considered an object in Python. Out of all the definitions with the same name, it uses the latest\n","definition for the method. Hence, we can define numerous methods with the same name, but we\n","can only use the latest defined method.\n","Method Overriding is a type of Run-time Polymorphism. A child class method overrides (or\n","provides its implementation) the parent class method of the same name, parameters, and return\n","type. It is used to over-write (redefine) a parent class method in the derived class."],"metadata":{"id":"ztACK_ug0m6N"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["4a)Aim:\n","Write a python program to implement Method Overriding"],"metadata":{"id":"PcBFkY7p0uuH"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["# class parent\n","\n","class Animal:\n","#properties\n","  multicellular = True\n","  eukaryotic = True\n","# function breathe\n","  def breathe(self):\n","    print(\"I breathe oxygen.\")\n","# function feed\n","  def feed(self):\n","    print(\"I eat food.\")\n","# child class\n","class Herbivorous(Animal):\n","# function feed\n","  def feed(self):\n","    print(\"I eat only plants. I am vegetarian.\")\n","herbi = Herbivorous()\n","herbi.feed()\n","# calling some other function\n","herbi.breathe()"],"metadata":{"id":"MUxBk7F70yBq","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1756918580540,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":31,"user":{"displayName":"AYUSH SINGH","userId":"00257767478009971220"}},"outputId":"e5e4581f-b7dc-49c8-99aa-77244ffda8c3","colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"}},"execution_count":1,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["I eat only plants. I am vegetarian.\n","I breathe oxygen.\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["4B)\n","Aim:\n","Write a python program to implement Method Overloading"],"metadata":{"id":"T7q5LkEW17Oo"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["class Student:\n","  def hello(self, name=None):\n","    if name is not None:\n","      print('Hey ' + name)\n","\n","    else:\n","      print('Hey ')\n","std = Student()\n","# Call the method\n","std.hello()\n","# Call the method and pass a parameter\n","std.hello('Jenni')"],"metadata":{"id":"aXiMiVgh2Ego","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1756918586512,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":6,"user":{"displayName":"AYUSH SINGH","userId":"00257767478009971220"}},"outputId":"4d8bf911-6ae8-41df-a070-2bd7d88a37e8","colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"}},"execution_count":2,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Hey \n","Hey Jenni\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["4C)AIM: Method Overriding with super()"],"metadata":{"id":"S0cvI7B47n5i"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["class Parent:\n","    def greet(self):\n","        print(\"Hello from Parent class\")\n","\n","class Child(Parent):\n","    def greet(self):\n","        super().greet()   # calling parent method\n","        print(\"Hello from Child class\")\n","\n","obj = Child()\n","obj.greet()"],"metadata":{"id":"huRRYvUO7wg8","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1756918588731,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":19,"user":{"displayName":"AYUSH SINGH","userId":"00257767478009971220"}},"outputId":"b1720f70-86f2-4873-e6ff-359323aa7180","colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"}},"execution_count":3,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Hello from Parent class\n","Hello from Child class\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["4D)AIM: constructor overloading using *args"],"metadata":{"id":"G5TKYH21-2tY"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["class Calculator:\n","    def __init__(self, *args):\n","        if len(args) == 0:\n","            print(\"No numbers provided\")\n","        elif len(args) == 1:\n","            print(\"Square of the number:\", args[0] ** 2)\n","        elif len(args) == 2:\n","            print(\"Sum of two numbers:\", args[0] + args[1])\n","        else:\n","            print(\"Product of all numbers:\", self.product(args))\n","\n","    def product(self, numbers):\n","        result = 1\n","        for num in numbers:\n","            result *= num\n","        return result\n","\n","# Different object creations\n","c1 = Calculator()\n","c2 = Calculator(5)\n","c3 = Calculator(3, 7)\n","c4 = Calculator(2, 3, 4)"],"metadata":{"id":"HjAw9OjD_AEj","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1756918590988,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":22,"user":{"displayName":"AYUSH SINGH","userId":"00257767478009971220"}},"outputId":"b75957bb-31aa-4e24-c031-bc87ef371dc3","colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"}},"execution_count":4,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["No numbers provided\n","Square of the number: 25\n","Sum of two numbers: 10\n","Product of all numbers: 24\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["4E. Demonstrate abstract class in python"],"metadata":{"id":"xUVJU61SncWI"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["from abc import ABC, abstractmethod\n","\n","class Bank(ABC):\n","    def bank_info(self):\n","        print(\"Welcome to bank\")\n","\n","    @abstractmethod\n","    def interest(self):\n","        pass\n","\n","class SBI(Bank):\n","    def balance(self):\n","        print(\"Balance is 100\")\n","\n","    # Implement abstract method\n","    def interest(self):\n","        print(\"Interest rate is 5%\")\n","\n","s = SBI()\n","s.bank_info()   # inherited method\n","s.balance()     # child class method\n","s.interest()    # implemented abstract method"],"metadata":{"id":"Vty336FpnPad","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1756918592894,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":22,"user":{"displayName":"AYUSH SINGH","userId":"00257767478009971220"}},"outputId":"84a8b9a4-b9d3-429c-a449-2940b8352bac","colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"}},"execution_count":5,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Welcome to bank\n","Balance is 100\n","Interest rate is 5%\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["Student Task:"],"metadata":{"id":"dJIsWzq92Prw"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["1)Method Overriding with super():\n","\n","Create a base class Vehicle with a method fuel_type() that prints \"Vehicles use different types of fuel\".\n","Create two subclasses:\n","\n","Car → overrides fuel_type() to print \"Cars use petrol or diesel\"\n","\n","ElectricCar → overrides fuel_type() to print \"Electric cars use electricity\" but also calls the parent method using super().\n","\n","2)Method Overloading with Default Arguments:\n","\n","Create a class Calculator that has a method add() which can:\n","\n","Add two numbers if two arguments are passed\n","\n","Add three numbers if three arguments are passed\n","\n","Return 0 if no argument is passed\n","\n","3)Constructor Overloading\n","\n","Write a Python program to demonstrate Constructor Overloading using default arguments.\n","Create a class Person that has a constructor which can accept:\n","\n","No arguments → print \"No details provided\"\n","\n","One argument (name) → print \"Name: <name>\"\n","\n","Two arguments (name, age) → print \"Name: <name>, Age: <age>\""],"metadata":{"id":"i8XHh3Cq2TFI"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["4)Multiple Inheritance\n","\n","Create a Python program to demonstrate Multiple Inheritance.\n","\n","Create a class Person with a method person_info() that prints \"I am a person\".\n","\n","Create a class Employee with a method employee_info() that prints \"I am an employee\".\n","\n","Create a class Manager that inherits both Person and Employee.\n","\n","In Manager, define a method manager_info() that prints \"I am a manager\".\n","\n","Create an object of the Manager class and call all three methods: person_info(), employee_info(), and manager_info()."],"metadata":{"id":"Sb9xquYfAxyN"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["class Vehicle:\n","    def fuel_type(self):\n","        print(\"Vehicles use different types of fuel\")\n","class Car(Vehicle):\n","    def fuel_type(self):\n","        print(\"Cars use petrol or diesel\")\n","class ElectricCar(Vehicle):\n","    def fuel_type(self):\n","        super().fuel_type()\n","        print(\"Electric cars use electricity\")\n","choice = input(\"Enter type (vehicle / car / electric): \").strip().lower()\n","\n","if choice == \"vehicle\":\n","    obj = Vehicle()\n","elif choice == \"car\":\n","    obj = Car()\n","elif choice == \"electric\":\n","    obj = ElectricCar()\n","else:\n","    print(\"Invalid choice! Defaulting to Vehicle.\")\n","    obj = Vehicle()\n","obj.fuel_type()"],"metadata":{"id":"6ddYBYHrRxCt","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1756915017246,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":17178,"user":{"displayName":"AYUSH SINGH","userId":"00257767478009971220"}},"outputId":"05ed058f-6dfe-4138-e402-0d4aa9ba10ac","colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"}},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Enter type (vehicle / car / electric): car\n","Cars use petrol or diesel\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["class Calculator:\n","    def add(self, a=0, b=0, c=0):\n","        return a + b + c\n","\n","\n","calc = Calculator()\n","\n","n = int(in